<i>'Tis the season to be jolly</i>

4
00:00:34.040 --> 00:00:37.040
<i>Fa-la-la-la-la</i>
<i>La-la-la-la</i>

5
00:00:37.120 --> 00:00:40.000
<i>Don we now our gay apparel</i>

6
00:00:40.080 --> 00:00:41.840
<i>Fa-la-la, la-la-la</i>
<i>La-la-la</i>

7
00:00:41.920 --> 00:00:43.000
(SULTAN BARKING)
(LAUGHING)

8
00:00:43.080 --> 00:00:45.960
<i>Troll the ancient Yuletide carol</i>

9
00:00:46.040 --> 00:00:49.880
<i>Fa-la-la-la-la</i>
<i>La-la-la-la</i>

10
00:00:49.960 --> 00:00:52.040
CHIP: Whoa!

11
00:00:53.120 --> 00:00:54.120
(BARKING)

12
00:00:54.240 --> 00:00:57.280
<i>Deck the halls</i>
<i>with boughs of holly</i>

13
00:00:57.360 --> 00:01:00.200
Ha-ha. There must be much,
much more holly.

14
00:01:00.280 --> 00:01:02.280
<i>'Tis the season to be...</i>

15
00:01:02.360 --> 00:01:03.680
What's this? There's too much holly.

16
00:01:03.760 --> 00:01:06.240
Whoa! Slow down, lad.

17
00:01:06.320 --> 00:01:09.280
<i>Don we now our gay apparel</i>

18
00:01:09.360 --> 00:01:12.040
No, no, no, no more mistletoe.

19
00:01:12.320 --> 00:01:14.240
(MRS. POTTS HUMMING)

20
00:01:15.520 --> 00:01:16.520
(LAUGHING)

21
00:01:16.600 --> 00:01:19.400
MRS. POTTS: Chip, away from
those presents, dear.

22
00:01:19.480 --> 00:01:20.760
(SULTAN BARKING)

23
00:01:20.840 --> 00:01:23.960
CHIP: Mama, I found one for me!

24
00:01:24.040 --> 00:01:25.880
Can I open it, Mama? Can I?

25
00:01:25.960 --> 00:01:29.160
-Well, just one.
-Oh, boy!

26
00:01:29.520 --> 00:01:31.560
It's good to see the boy
having a proper Christmas.

27
00:01:31.640 --> 00:01:32.680
(SNARLING)

28
00:01:32.760 --> 00:01:34.720
Not like last year.

29
00:01:34.880 --> 00:01:38.280
(CHUCKLES) Yes.
This is much more agreeable.

30
00:01:38.360 --> 00:01:41.200
Well, I thought last year
was quite nice.

31
00:01:41.280 --> 00:01:45.480
Yes, well, I suppose I...
I did manage to save Christmas.

32
00:01:45.560 --> 00:01:48.000
-You?
-Yes, me.

33
00:01:48.080 --> 00:01:49.080
(LAUGHING)

34
00:01:49.160 --> 00:01:51.440
If not for my skillful
and decisive leadership,

35
00:01:51.520 --> 00:01:52.720
all would've been lost.

36
00:01:52.800 --> 00:01:56.640
Leadership? Ha!
You could not lead a horse to water.

37
00:01:56.720 --> 00:01:58.120
COGSWORTH:
What are you yammering about?

38
00:01:58.200 --> 00:01:59.240
(SIGHS)

39
00:01:59.320 --> 00:02:00.520
It was all my idea.

40
00:02:00.640 --> 00:02:03.480
Your idea?
Everyone knows it was mine.

41
00:02:03.600 --> 00:02:08.040
Heavens. How many times are
we going to have to go over this story?

42
00:02:08.120 --> 00:02:12.480
-Story?
-Until someone gets his facts straight.

43
00:02:12.560 --> 00:02:15.360
-Why don't you tell it, Mama?
-COGSWORTH: Capital idea.

44
00:02:15.440 --> 00:02:17.600
Well, I don't know.

45
00:02:17.680 --> 00:02:19.200
Come now, Mrs. Potts.

46
00:02:19.280 --> 00:02:22.240
Surely you recall
how I saved Christmas.

47
00:02:22.320 --> 00:02:24.520
Tut-tut-tut-tut. No leading the witness.

48
00:02:24.600 --> 00:02:27.040
Please, Mama, tell the story.

49
00:02:27.120 --> 00:02:29.400
Oh, all right.

50
00:02:29.480 --> 00:02:33.520
LUMIERE: Ah! Now we will hear
what really happened.

51
00:02:33.600 --> 00:02:35.680
Well, let's see.

52
00:02:35.760 --> 00:02:38.880
Belle, terrified by the master's anger,

53
00:02:38.960 --> 00:02:40.520
ran away from the castle

54
00:02:40.600 --> 00:02:44.200
straight into a pack of wolves.

55
00:02:44.280 --> 00:02:46.920
But the master saved her.

56
00:02:47.000 --> 00:02:48.960
<i>They began to be friends.</i>

57
00:02:49.040 --> 00:02:50.320
LUMIERE: <i>Ah-ah-ah.</i>

58
00:02:50.400 --> 00:02:52.800
<i>That's where I came in.</i>

59
00:02:54.280 --> 00:02:57.400
CHIP: Where could he be?
MRS. POTTS: Goodness knows.

60
00:02:57.480 --> 00:03:00.040
We've searched every last corner.

61
00:03:00.120 --> 00:03:03.640
COGSWORTH: I'm beginning to think
he's not in the castle at all.

62
00:03:05.760 --> 00:03:08.000
<i>Voil√†!</i> There he is!

63
00:03:08.080 --> 00:03:10.840
-Wonderful!
-(GASPS) No time to waste.

64
00:03:10.960 --> 00:03:12.800
We must find a way
to get them together.

65
00:03:12.880 --> 00:03:15.720
LUMIERE: Let's go! Love will not wait.

66
00:03:15.840 --> 00:03:19.200
You really think she's the one?
Will she break the spell?

67
00:03:19.280 --> 00:03:21.800
(PANTING) I knew it from the moment
I set eyes on her.

68
00:03:21.880 --> 00:03:26.400
If anyone can reach the master,
Belle can. Such a kind soul.

69
00:03:27.000 --> 00:03:28.240
LUMIERE: And her looks
don't hurt either.

70
00:03:28.320 --> 00:03:29.320
(CHIP GIGGLING)

71
00:03:29.400 --> 00:03:31.160
Wait for me! (PANTING)

72
00:03:39.600 --> 00:03:42.440
-Hi, Belle.
-Oh, hello.

73
00:03:42.960 --> 00:03:45.240
Chip, do you know what day it is?

74
00:03:45.320 --> 00:03:48.840
Well, it's not Tuesday...

75
00:03:48.920 --> 00:03:52.640
No, silly. Today is December 24th.

76
00:03:52.720 --> 00:03:56.920
-The day before Christmas.
-And what a beautiful day it is.

77
00:03:57.000 --> 00:03:59.760
A wonderful day for a morning stroll.

78
00:03:59.880 --> 00:04:03.920
Yes, yes. Nothing starts the day
like a brisk walk around the grounds.

79
00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:06.520
CHIP: Yeah!
Or you could go ice-skating.

80
00:04:06.640 --> 00:04:08.920
-Ha-ha. Wahoo!
-Yes, fresh air, exercise. Ha-ha.

81
00:04:09.000 --> 00:04:11.440
-(BACK CREAKING)
-In moderation, of course.

82
00:04:11.520 --> 00:04:12.560
(SNORING)

83
00:04:12.640 --> 00:04:15.320
MRS. POTTS: Come along, Belle, dear.
The great outdoors awaits.

84
00:04:15.440 --> 00:04:17.360
CHIP: Yeah, let's go!

85
00:04:20.320 --> 00:04:22.320
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

86
00:04:25.280 --> 00:04:26.360
(GROWLING)

87
00:04:26.480 --> 00:04:28.200
Oh. Good morning.

88
00:04:28.280 --> 00:04:31.480
Huh? Whoa... (GRUNTS)

89
00:04:31.560 --> 00:04:32.640
(LOW GROWL)

90
00:04:32.720 --> 00:04:35.400
Oh, dear. Are you all right?

91
00:04:36.240 --> 00:04:38.320
Uh... Uh...

92
00:04:40.080 --> 00:04:45.160
I fell and I landed on my...
On... On the ice.

93
00:04:45.240 --> 00:04:47.240
It's pretty slippery.

94
00:04:47.720 --> 00:04:50.560
Yes, it's slippery.

95
00:04:51.440 --> 00:04:53.960
This is a perfect day for skating.

96
00:04:54.760 --> 00:04:57.000
Come on. (GIGGLING)

97
00:04:57.640 --> 00:04:58.880
Hmm?

98
00:04:59.760 --> 00:05:01.440
Come on.

99
00:05:01.520 --> 00:05:02.880
No.

100
00:05:02.960 --> 00:05:04.080
(GRUNTS)

101
00:05:04.720 --> 00:05:09.000
-Go on, Master. It might be fun.
-Go for it!

102
00:05:09.120 --> 00:05:11.040
Hmm. Hmm?

103
00:05:11.160 --> 00:05:13.280
(CHIP LAUGHING)
(BARKING)

104
00:05:13.440 --> 00:05:15.120
CHIP: Come on!
COGSWORTH: Not so fast.

105
00:05:15.760 --> 00:05:16.800
Ooo-ooo la-la.

106
00:05:16.880 --> 00:05:17.920
(COGSWORTH SIGHS)

107
00:05:18.000 --> 00:05:20.800
Come on. Why don't you try it like this?

108
00:05:20.920 --> 00:05:25.600
One, two, three. One, two, three.
See? It's easy.

109
00:05:27.480 --> 00:05:30.080
One, two, three.

110
00:05:30.160 --> 00:05:33.280
One, two, three.

111
00:05:33.440 --> 00:05:34.560
Ho-ho-ho.

112
00:05:34.640 --> 00:05:37.200
Yes, I think this may work.

113
00:05:37.280 --> 00:05:38.560
(ALL LAUGHING)

114
00:05:39.160 --> 00:05:41.640
(GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING)

115
00:05:54.320 --> 00:05:56.000
(CONTINUES PLAYING)

116
00:05:59.440 --> 00:06:01.320
(MUSIC ENDS)

117
00:06:01.480 --> 00:06:05.120
Bravo! Bravo! Encore!

118
00:06:05.320 --> 00:06:07.000
(CHUCKLES)

119
00:06:07.080 --> 00:06:09.960
Fife, you approve?

120
00:06:10.040 --> 00:06:13.000
Oh, Maestro, it's magnificent!

121
00:06:13.080 --> 00:06:16.320
Oh, come along. It's merely an opera

122
00:06:18.640 --> 00:06:22.480
to bring the house down. (LAUGHING)

123
00:06:22.680 --> 00:06:24.000
-Ooh!
-(GRUNTING)

124
00:06:25.080 --> 00:06:27.600
Is there a part for a piccolo?

125
00:06:27.680 --> 00:06:29.680
Absolutely.

126
00:06:29.960 --> 00:06:31.680
(MELODIC MUSIC PLAYING)

127
00:06:34.720 --> 00:06:35.760
(LAUGHING)

128
00:06:35.840 --> 00:06:39.440
Solo for Fife in B-flat.

129
00:06:39.520 --> 00:06:43.520
-Ooh. I'd do anything for a solo.
-Yes.

130
00:06:44.520 --> 00:06:48.040
I know. Now, Fifey,

131
00:06:48.120 --> 00:06:50.280
in the midst of my crescendo,

132
00:06:50.360 --> 00:06:53.960
I thought I heard merriment
outside the window.

133
00:06:54.040 --> 00:06:56.440
Have a little look-see, will you?

134
00:06:56.560 --> 00:06:58.200
(LAUGHING CONTINUES)

135
00:06:58.720 --> 00:07:01.640
Wow! Would you look at that?

136
00:07:01.720 --> 00:07:05.480
Well, I think I might.
I'll just pick myself up and...

137
00:07:05.560 --> 00:07:06.560
Oh!

138
00:07:06.640 --> 00:07:09.280
What's this? Heavens, look.

139
00:07:09.360 --> 00:07:11.840
I'm bolted to the wall!

140
00:07:11.920 --> 00:07:13.720
Oh, right.

141
00:07:13.800 --> 00:07:15.320
(NERVOUS CHUCKLE)

142
00:07:15.400 --> 00:07:18.360
Um, the master is skating.

143
00:07:18.440 --> 00:07:22.000
Skating? Why on earth
would he do a thing like that?

144
00:07:22.080 --> 00:07:25.200
Probably because that
pretty girl is holding his hand.

145
00:07:25.280 --> 00:07:27.720
-What? Belle?
-Hey.

146
00:07:28.320 --> 00:07:32.080
Maybe if she falls in love with him,
the spell will be broken,

147
00:07:32.160 --> 00:07:34.320
and we'll be human again!

148
00:07:34.400 --> 00:07:36.200
(BLARING)
(SCREAMS)

149
00:07:36.280 --> 00:07:38.200
Trust me, Fife.

150
00:07:38.280 --> 00:07:41.800
-Humanity is entirely overrated.
-(GRUNTS)

151
00:07:41.880 --> 00:07:44.680
Before the enchantment,
there was no need

152
00:07:44.760 --> 00:07:48.480
for my particular brand of genius.

153
00:07:48.920 --> 00:07:52.240
But now the master needs my melodies

154
00:07:52.320 --> 00:07:55.040
to feed his tormented soul.

155
00:07:55.640 --> 00:07:58.200
I am his confidant

156
00:07:58.800 --> 00:08:00.800
and his best friend.

157
00:08:01.680 --> 00:08:05.560
And I won't let some peasant girl
ruin it for me!

158
00:08:05.640 --> 00:08:06.640
(MUSIC BLARING)

159
00:08:06.760 --> 00:08:11.040
Fife, see to it that this blossoming love

160
00:08:11.120 --> 00:08:13.440
withers on the vine.

161
00:08:13.960 --> 00:08:17.000
Yes, Maestro Forte. (CHUCKLES)

162
00:08:17.280 --> 00:08:19.440
One, two, three.

163
00:08:19.520 --> 00:08:22.680
One, two, three. One, two, three.
One, two, three.

164
00:08:22.760 --> 00:08:24.680
I think I've got it! (GRUNTS)

165
00:08:24.760 --> 00:08:25.880
(GIGGLES)

166
00:08:27.800 --> 00:08:29.040
(PANTING)

167
00:08:30.440 --> 00:08:32.680
Hey, down in front. I wanna see.

168
00:08:32.760 --> 00:08:35.120
Let me see. I wanna see, too!

169
00:08:35.320 --> 00:08:36.360
(HIGH-PITCHED WHISTLE)

170
00:08:36.440 --> 00:08:37.480
ALL: Shh!

171
00:08:37.800 --> 00:08:38.800
(GROANS)

172
00:08:38.880 --> 00:08:42.080
Quiet. Oh, this is very promising.

173
00:08:42.160 --> 00:08:44.680
Ah, yes, there is something in the air.

174
00:08:44.760 --> 00:08:47.080
-(SULTAN BARKS)
-Could it be love?

175
00:08:47.160 --> 00:08:49.120
Love? Oh, oh, oh, ooh.

176
00:08:49.200 --> 00:08:50.880
Uh. Oh. Oh.

177
00:08:50.960 --> 00:08:52.560
I've got to stop them.

178
00:08:52.640 --> 00:08:53.640
Oh!

179
00:08:54.720 --> 00:08:55.960
(SCREAMING)

180
00:08:56.040 --> 00:08:58.440
Help!

181
00:08:58.840 --> 00:09:01.520
Whoa-oh-oh-oh!

182
00:09:01.800 --> 00:09:03.920
What's that little toot up to?

183
00:09:04.000 --> 00:09:05.520
Whoa!

184
00:09:11.280 --> 00:09:13.280
Mmm-mmm. (CHUCKLES)

185
00:09:15.400 --> 00:09:17.480
Stop! (GRUNTS)

186
00:09:17.560 --> 00:09:19.360
(BOTH SHOUTING)

187
00:09:20.520 --> 00:09:21.880
(PANTING)

188
00:09:21.960 --> 00:09:23.200
(GRUNTING)

189
00:09:26.600 --> 00:09:28.120
(GROANS)

190
00:09:30.360 --> 00:09:31.680
(SIGHS)

191
00:09:33.760 --> 00:09:34.720
(SPITS)

192
00:09:34.840 --> 00:09:35.840
(MOANS)

193
00:09:36.160 --> 00:09:38.440
It's a Christmas angel, see?

194
00:09:38.880 --> 00:09:40.440
(LOW GROWL)

195
00:09:40.640 --> 00:09:41.840
Oh.

196
00:09:44.200 --> 00:09:46.280
This is no angel.

197
00:09:46.720 --> 00:09:49.560
It's the shadow of a monster.

198
00:09:49.800 --> 00:09:51.120
(ROARING)

199
00:09:52.960 --> 00:09:54.520
(ROARING CONTINUES)

200
00:09:55.560 --> 00:09:56.920
(CHUCKLING)

201
00:09:57.360 --> 00:10:00.600
Oh, Forte is going to be so proud of me.

202
00:10:00.880 --> 00:10:02.280
(PANTING)

203
00:10:04.880 --> 00:10:07.200
I don't know why I bother.

204
00:10:07.440 --> 00:10:08.560
(SIGHS)

205
00:10:08.880 --> 00:10:11.040
Now he's worse than ever.

206
00:10:11.520 --> 00:10:13.760
Don't lose heart, dearest.

207
00:10:15.360 --> 00:10:16.360
(FORTE PLAYING GLOOMY MUSIC)

208
00:10:21.240 --> 00:10:22.560
(GROWLING)

209
00:10:27.920 --> 00:10:31.760
I hate Christmas. (GRUNTS)

210
00:10:32.920 --> 00:10:34.400
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

211
00:10:40.960 --> 00:10:43.640
The music helps?

212
00:10:43.720 --> 00:10:47.920
Your music is the only thing
that helps me forget. (LOW GROWL)

213
00:10:48.000 --> 00:10:50.520
Don't worry, old friend.

214
00:10:50.600 --> 00:10:52.960
I'm here for you,

215
00:10:53.040 --> 00:10:55.360
just as I have been,

216
00:10:55.440 --> 00:10:58.160
just as I always will be.

217
00:10:59.840 --> 00:11:01.920
Why is the beast such a grump?

218
00:11:02.000 --> 00:11:04.640
I don't know. He's always like that.

219
00:11:05.320 --> 00:11:07.680
-Even at Christmas?
-Yep.

220
00:11:08.640 --> 00:11:11.240
Belle, what's Christmas?

221
00:11:11.320 --> 00:11:13.760
Oh, Chip, you must know
about Christmas.

222
00:11:13.840 --> 00:11:17.280
Stockings in front of the fire? Tree?

223
00:11:17.360 --> 00:11:19.720
Tinsel? Presents?

224
00:11:19.800 --> 00:11:21.880
Presents? Do I get one?

225
00:11:22.480 --> 00:11:25.440
Of course. Everyone gets
a present on Christmas.

226
00:11:25.520 --> 00:11:28.960
-Oh, even the master?
-Yes, even the master.

227
00:11:29.080 --> 00:11:32.320
-What are you gonna get him?
-I don't really know him well enough

228
00:11:32.400 --> 00:11:34.480
to know what he would want.

229
00:11:34.560 --> 00:11:38.720
-What would you want?
-Well, what I love most

230
00:11:38.840 --> 00:11:42.560
in the world are my books, my stories.

231
00:11:42.640 --> 00:11:45.160
Why don't you get the master a story?

232
00:11:45.240 --> 00:11:48.560
You're right, Chip. A story.

233
00:11:50.920 --> 00:11:53.920
(SINGING) <i>When I get to know him</i>

234
00:11:54.000 --> 00:11:57.400
<i>We'll find more things to say</i>

235
00:11:57.480 --> 00:12:00.480
<i>One day I will reach him</i>

236
00:12:00.560 --> 00:12:03.960
<i>There has to be a way</i>

237
00:12:04.040 --> 00:12:06.920
<i>Everyone needs someone</i>

238
00:12:07.000 --> 00:12:10.400
<i>He must need someone, too</i>

239
00:12:10.480 --> 00:12:13.680
<i>When I get to know him better</i>

240
00:12:13.760 --> 00:12:17.360
<i>Here's what I will do</i>

241
00:12:18.520 --> 00:12:21.280
<i>I'll read him stories</i>

242
00:12:21.360 --> 00:12:24.800
<i>From picture books</i>
<i>all filled with wonder</i>

243
00:12:24.880 --> 00:12:27.800
<i>Magic worlds where the impossible</i>

244
00:12:27.880 --> 00:12:31.080
<i>Becomes the everyday</i>

245
00:12:31.160 --> 00:12:34.280
<i>We'll find a mountaintop</i>

246
00:12:34.360 --> 00:12:37.560
<i>And some moonbeams to sit under</i>

247
00:12:37.640 --> 00:12:43.800
<i>I'll lead because I know the way</i>

248
00:12:43.880 --> 00:12:47.000
<i>So much to discover</i>

249
00:12:47.120 --> 00:12:50.440
<i>I do it all the time</i>

250
00:12:50.520 --> 00:12:53.560
<i>I could live inside bright pages</i>

251
00:12:53.640 --> 00:12:56.600
<i>Where the words all rhyme</i>

252
00:12:56.680 --> 00:12:59.440
