494
00:26:25.520 --> 00:26:26.840
(FIRE CRACKLING)

495
00:26:30.560 --> 00:26:32.480
Hey, hey, hey. Come on.
Get out of the way.

496
00:26:32.560 --> 00:26:34.960
-We're workin' here.
-(GASPS)

497
00:26:35.040 --> 00:26:38.520
-Excuse me.
-Let's go. Let's go.

498
00:26:38.600 --> 00:26:41.640
All right, you guys.
Now, get back to work.

499
00:26:41.720 --> 00:26:44.320
The castle doesn't heat itself,
you know.

500
00:26:44.400 --> 00:26:45.480
(SPEAKING YIDDISH)

501
00:26:45.560 --> 00:26:48.120
So, what can I do you for, lady?

502
00:26:48.200 --> 00:26:51.400
-I'm looking for a log.
-All right. Logs we got.

503
00:26:51.480 --> 00:26:54.560
What do you want? Hard wood?
Soft wood? We got it all.

504
00:26:54.640 --> 00:26:56.720
We got birch, maple, pine, oak...

505
00:26:56.800 --> 00:26:59.200
-(BANGING)
-(SHOUTS) Concrete.

506
00:26:59.280 --> 00:27:02.000
-(TWITTERING)
-My head. Don't worry. It'll pass.

507
00:27:02.080 --> 00:27:04.280
So, make up your mind already.

508
00:27:04.360 --> 00:27:07.080
Is it all right if I just browse?

509
00:27:07.160 --> 00:27:10.480
Suit yourself. Take your time.
Me, I got work to do.

510
00:27:11.720 --> 00:27:12.720
Huh.

511
00:27:12.800 --> 00:27:13.800
(LOUD BANGING)

512
00:27:13.880 --> 00:27:14.880
Hmm.

513
00:27:15.720 --> 00:27:16.800
(BANGING)

514
00:27:16.880 --> 00:27:18.000
(HISSING)

515
00:27:18.840 --> 00:27:20.000
(ALL GASPING)

516
00:27:20.880 --> 00:27:22.720
(WHISTLE BLOWING)

517
00:27:23.400 --> 00:27:24.520
(BLARING)

518
00:27:26.760 --> 00:27:28.400
-Whew.
-(ALL SIGH)

519
00:27:28.480 --> 00:27:31.040
Hey, what am I payin' you for,
being boring?

520
00:27:31.120 --> 00:27:34.240
Do that on your own time.
Get out of here!

521
00:27:34.720 --> 00:27:35.880
(WORKERS CHATTERING)

522
00:27:35.960 --> 00:27:37.320
Yes.

523
00:27:38.720 --> 00:27:40.080
Oh!

524
00:27:40.640 --> 00:27:41.920
(HUMMING)

525
00:27:45.200 --> 00:27:46.400
(GROWLING)
(GASPS)

526
00:27:47.680 --> 00:27:48.720
(HUMMING)

527
00:27:48.800 --> 00:27:50.720
What are you hiding?

528
00:27:50.800 --> 00:27:51.960
(HUFFING)

529
00:27:53.120 --> 00:27:54.440
(GROWLS)

530
00:27:58.400 --> 00:28:00.680
It's a Yule log.

531
00:28:00.920 --> 00:28:01.960
Huh?

532
00:28:02.040 --> 00:28:03.760
A... A Yule log.

533
00:28:04.640 --> 00:28:07.040
It's a wonderful tradition.

534
00:28:07.160 --> 00:28:10.400
One log is chosen and everyone
in the house touches it

535
00:28:10.480 --> 00:28:12.640
and makes a Christmas wish.

536
00:28:13.080 --> 00:28:15.400
Mmm, wishes are stupid.

537
00:28:15.840 --> 00:28:17.000
(GROWLS)

538
00:28:17.320 --> 00:28:20.520
You made a Christmas wish last year.

539
00:28:20.600 --> 00:28:24.360
Is this what you wished for? (ROARING)

540
00:28:24.440 --> 00:28:25.840
(BATS SCREECHING)

541
00:28:27.760 --> 00:28:29.000
No.

542
00:28:29.320 --> 00:28:30.400
(GRUNTS)

543
00:28:31.160 --> 00:28:33.280
But I will keep wishing.

544
00:28:33.680 --> 00:28:35.640
And when the log is burned
on Christmas morning...

545
00:28:35.720 --> 00:28:37.600
There will be no Christmas.

546
00:28:37.680 --> 00:28:42.400
-But...
-No! I am the master here.

547
00:28:42.480 --> 00:28:45.120
How can you be so selfish?

548
00:28:45.240 --> 00:28:48.320
You cannot possibly understand.

549
00:28:48.400 --> 00:28:51.640
You have no idea
what it's like to lose everything,

550
00:28:51.720 --> 00:28:53.920
to be trapped in your own castle,

551
00:28:54.040 --> 00:28:56.280
to be a... A... A...

552
00:28:56.360 --> 00:28:57.840
Prisoner?

553
00:28:59.560 --> 00:29:03.040
The only one holding us prisoner here
is you.

554
00:29:03.120 --> 00:29:05.200
Well, I'm not giving up.

555
00:29:10.440 --> 00:29:12.120
Prisoner.

556
00:29:29.560 --> 00:29:30.760
(SIGHS)

557
00:29:31.680 --> 00:29:34.440
CHIP: Hiya, Belle.
You should see the ballroom.

558
00:29:34.520 --> 00:29:37.080
It's all decorated and pretty
and there's garlands everywhere.

559
00:29:37.160 --> 00:29:39.120
I think the master's gonna
be really excited

560
00:29:39.200 --> 00:29:41.240
when he finds out about Christmas.

561
00:29:41.320 --> 00:29:44.400
Well, he... He already knows.

562
00:29:44.480 --> 00:29:47.280
Really? Was he excited?

563
00:29:47.360 --> 00:29:50.480
Actually, Chip, he's forbidden it.

564
00:29:51.600 --> 00:29:55.320
But I thought
he couldn't forbid Christmas.

565
00:29:56.720 --> 00:29:59.480
You know, Chip, he can't.

566
00:29:59.560 --> 00:30:01.840
We'll have Christmas
with or without him.

567
00:30:01.920 --> 00:30:07.040
Hurray! Can we get a tree now, Belle?
It's the only thing we're missing.

568
00:30:07.120 --> 00:30:10.080
All right, then. Let's go get a tree.

569
00:30:10.600 --> 00:30:12.240
But first...

570
00:30:13.200 --> 00:30:14.360
Shh.

571
00:30:24.840 --> 00:30:28.280
(WHISPERING) Psst, Belle.
The master. Hurry.

572
00:30:30.400 --> 00:30:31.800
(GROWLING)

573
00:30:40.480 --> 00:30:41.560
(LAUGHING)

574
00:30:41.640 --> 00:30:42.680
(SULTAN BARKING)

575
00:30:43.280 --> 00:30:45.000
(LAUGHING CONTINUES)

576
00:30:45.080 --> 00:30:46.440
(PANTING)

577
00:30:47.480 --> 00:30:48.960
(PANTING)

578
00:30:49.480 --> 00:30:51.440
What about this one?

579
00:30:54.320 --> 00:30:55.640
Mmm...

580
00:30:58.400 --> 00:30:59.920
(DISAPPROVINGLY) Mmm.

581
00:31:01.080 --> 00:31:04.800
Nah, too skinny. Come on.

582
00:31:06.040 --> 00:31:07.080
(EXHALES)

583
00:31:07.160 --> 00:31:08.160
(AXE GROANS)

584
00:31:08.240 --> 00:31:10.560
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

585
00:31:10.800 --> 00:31:12.680
(DOOR CREAKING)

586
00:31:17.520 --> 00:31:18.880
Ooo la-la.

587
00:31:20.320 --> 00:31:24.320
-Ohh, Lumiere.
-She's beautiful, no?

588
00:31:24.400 --> 00:31:27.000
Yes, and I'm hideous.

589
00:31:27.080 --> 00:31:29.440
(WHISPERING) Not to mention
ill-tempered.

590
00:31:29.520 --> 00:31:32.720
What? What is that?

591
00:31:32.800 --> 00:31:35.680
Ooh, it looks like a Christmas present.

592
00:31:36.000 --> 00:31:37.240
(ROARS)

593
00:31:43.760 --> 00:31:46.280
Oh-ho-ho. It's for you, master.

594
00:31:46.360 --> 00:31:48.960
It's from a girl.

595
00:31:50.600 --> 00:31:54.320
-Mrs. Potts?
-No. From Belle.

596
00:31:56.000 --> 00:31:57.280
Belle?

597
00:32:00.760 --> 00:32:03.240
Uh-uh-uh. Master, you can't open it.

598
00:32:03.360 --> 00:32:05.680
Well, why not? It's for me, isn't it?

599
00:32:05.760 --> 00:32:08.080
Because it's not yet Christmas.

600
00:32:08.160 --> 00:32:09.560
(GROWLS)

601
00:32:09.640 --> 00:32:14.360
Master, we all understand
how you feel about Christmas.

602
00:32:14.440 --> 00:32:19.240
But when a woman gives a man a gift,
she's saying, "I care about you."

603
00:32:19.400 --> 00:32:20.520
Hmm.

604
00:32:20.600 --> 00:32:22.600
But I don't have a gift for her.

605
00:32:22.680 --> 00:32:24.440
It is not too late.

606
00:32:24.520 --> 00:32:25.600
(SIGHS)

607
00:32:26.440 --> 00:32:30.120
Well, I guess I could
get her a little something.

608
00:32:30.720 --> 00:32:32.640
(MUSIC PLAYING)

609
00:32:35.080 --> 00:32:37.440
Forte, stop the noise!

610
00:32:37.520 --> 00:32:40.160
Noise? Noise?

611
00:32:40.760 --> 00:32:42.600
This is my masterpiece.

612
00:32:42.680 --> 00:32:43.800
(GROWLS)

613
00:32:43.880 --> 00:32:45.440
Master.

614
00:32:46.600 --> 00:32:48.640
I... I want you to compose a song.

615
00:32:48.720 --> 00:32:52.040
-It's a present for Belle.
-What? Belle?

616
00:32:53.200 --> 00:32:55.840
And make it happy!

617
00:32:55.920 --> 00:32:59.840
Oh, but happiness is so depressing.

618
00:33:00.480 --> 00:33:03.600
What's next? Love songs?

619
00:33:03.840 --> 00:33:05.400
(GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING)
(FIFE PANTING)

620
00:33:05.480 --> 00:33:07.680
Wedding marches?

621
00:33:09.600 --> 00:33:13.120
It's all that girl's fault.

622
00:33:13.320 --> 00:33:14.320
(BARKING)

623
00:33:14.400 --> 00:33:15.400
(SNARLING)

624
00:33:15.480 --> 00:33:17.320
What about this one?

625
00:33:17.400 --> 00:33:22.240
-Hmm, too wiggly.
-Too wiggly.

626
00:33:22.320 --> 00:33:23.520
Fife!

627
00:33:23.600 --> 00:33:24.760
(BLARING)

628
00:33:24.840 --> 00:33:26.400
(GASPING)

629
00:33:26.480 --> 00:33:27.600
Pay attention.

630
00:33:27.680 --> 00:33:32.400
I need you to pace when I think.
The girl is evil, I tell you.

631
00:33:32.480 --> 00:33:34.600
She pulls him from my grasp.

632
00:33:34.680 --> 00:33:37.360
She fills his head with dreams of love

633
00:33:37.440 --> 00:33:40.080
and hope and Christmas!

634
00:33:40.200 --> 00:33:43.760
Well, what you gonna do?
You can't stop Christmas. (CHUCKLES)

635
00:33:43.840 --> 00:33:48.880
No, but I can stop the girl.

636
00:33:51.400 --> 00:33:52.800
(BARKING)

637
00:33:52.880 --> 00:33:56.400
Chip, this is the last one.

638
00:33:56.480 --> 00:34:00.400
That's not it. That's just a weed
wishing it was a tree.

639
00:34:00.480 --> 00:34:03.880
Chip, we've looked
at every tree on the grounds.

640
00:34:03.960 --> 00:34:06.720
But it's more this way than that.

641
00:34:06.800 --> 00:34:08.680
It will have to do.

642
00:34:09.120 --> 00:34:10.080
(AXE GROANS)

643
00:34:10.160 --> 00:34:11.480
(SPEAKING YIDDISH)

644
00:34:11.560 --> 00:34:14.440
-What a headache I have.
-I'm sorry.

645
00:34:14.520 --> 00:34:16.320
I... I'll get a saw.

646
00:34:16.400 --> 00:34:19.440
No, that's fine.
I don't want I should put you out.

647
00:34:19.520 --> 00:34:21.240
Oh, all right.

648
00:34:22.920 --> 00:34:26.520
Do you have some oil?
I just thought a little massage...

649
00:34:26.600 --> 00:34:29.560
But if it's no, it's no. Go on.
What are you waiting for?

650
00:34:29.640 --> 00:34:31.720
Knock yourself out.

651
00:34:32.680 --> 00:34:34.960
You never get headaches, I guess.
Lucky you.

652
00:34:35.040 --> 00:34:38.280
-Really, I can get a saw.
-Who wants a saw?

653
00:34:38.360 --> 00:34:41.720
I said go ahead with the whacking
and the hitting. Who's stopping you?

654
00:34:41.800 --> 00:34:43.640
-(SLOW MELODIC MUSIC PLAYING)
-BELLE: Shh.

655
00:34:43.720 --> 00:34:45.520
What is that?

656
00:34:52.320 --> 00:34:53.480
Ohh.

657
00:34:54.400 --> 00:34:56.440
It's beautiful.

658
00:35:00.160 --> 00:35:03.840
And now for a little Fife.

659
00:35:03.920 --> 00:35:05.040
(INHALES DEEPLY)

660
00:35:05.160 --> 00:35:06.400
(HIGH-PITCHED WHISTLING)

661
00:35:06.520 --> 00:35:07.720
(HOWLING)

662
00:35:08.720 --> 00:35:09.920
(BARKING)

663
00:35:11.280 --> 00:35:13.000
Sultan, wait!

664
00:35:14.480 --> 00:35:18.760
Don't worry yourself about me.
I'll just sit here. Snow is fine.

665
00:35:19.240 --> 00:35:21.400
A little wet, but who's complaining?

666
00:35:21.760 --> 00:35:26.280
Yes, my dear. Come to me.

667
00:35:26.720 --> 00:35:29.360
Come here, boy. Come here.

668
00:35:35.400 --> 00:35:36.600
(BARKING CONTINUES)

669
00:35:36.880 --> 00:35:37.880
(GASPS)

670
00:35:37.960 --> 00:35:41.360
-Good doggy. Nice doggy.
-(GROWLING)

671
00:35:41.440 --> 00:35:42.480
(SCREAMS)

672
00:35:42.560 --> 00:35:45.040
BELLE: Sultan?
FIFE: Back off, doggy.

673
00:35:46.200 --> 00:35:47.280
Oh.

674
00:35:47.880 --> 00:35:49.440
Hello?

675
00:35:51.360 --> 00:35:52.720
Hello?

676
00:35:52.800 --> 00:35:55.480
CHIP: (SHUDDERING)
Well, maybe there's nobody here.

677
00:35:56.240 --> 00:35:59.040
Maybe we should go.

678
00:35:59.120 --> 00:36:00.200
(SULTAN BARKING)

679
00:36:00.280 --> 00:36:02.480
BELLE: What's the matter, Sultan?

680
00:36:03.680 --> 00:36:04.880
(WHIMPERING)

681
00:36:05.960 --> 00:36:10.080
Oh, hello. I don't believe we've met.
I... I'm Belle.

682
00:36:10.360 --> 00:36:13.200
-And you are?
-Fife.

683
00:36:13.560 --> 00:36:16.160
-(GROWLING)
-Down, boy, down.

684
00:36:16.240 --> 00:36:18.800
We heard the most beautiful music.

685
00:36:19.280 --> 00:36:21.560
-Was it you?
-(GIGGLES) Me?

686
00:36:21.640 --> 00:36:24.960
You thought that was me?

687
00:36:25.040 --> 00:36:26.080
(HIGH-PITCHED WHISTLING)

688
00:36:26.200 --> 00:36:27.440
(WHIMPERING)

689
00:36:27.800 --> 00:36:28.840
(CHUCKLES)

690
00:36:28.920 --> 00:36:30.600
FORTE: <i>Mademoiselle,</i> please.

691
00:36:30.680 --> 00:36:31.720
(GASPS)

692
00:36:31.800 --> 00:36:34.880
I am Maestro Forte,

693
00:36:35.000 --> 00:36:39.400
court composer
and your most humble servant.

694
00:36:39.480 --> 00:36:42.640
Pleased to meet you, <i>Monsieur</i> Forte.
I'm Belle.

695
00:36:42.760 --> 00:36:47.120
Yes. The entire castle is talking
about you, child.

696
00:36:47.200 --> 00:36:52.000
They say you're planning
a Christmas gala. Marvelous idea.

697
00:36:52.080 --> 00:36:57.240
The very thing to shatter
the master's dark and gloomy past.

698
00:36:57.360 --> 00:37:01.600
But you must make this
the grandest celebration ever.

699
00:37:01.680 --> 00:37:03.080
-Have you gifts?
-Yep.

700
00:37:03.200 --> 00:37:04.160
-Food?
-Yep.

701
00:37:04.240 --> 00:37:06.360
-Garlands, ribbons, wreaths?
-Check.

702
00:37:06.440 --> 00:37:08.600
Spangles and "fandangles"?

703
00:37:08.680 --> 00:37:11.520
The trinkets, the trimmings,
the trappings?

704
00:37:11.600 --> 00:37:15.520
-Yep, we got 'em all.
-A tree?

705
00:37:17.360 --> 00:37:19.760
See, Belle? I told you.

706
00:37:19.880 --> 00:37:21.440
Well, we found one.

707
00:37:21.520 --> 00:37:24.760
But it was on the piddlin' side of puny.

708
00:37:24.840 --> 00:37:26.440
(CHUCKLING)

709
00:37:26.520 --> 00:37:29.880
But did you look in the Black Forest?

710
00:37:30.400 --> 00:37:32.880
There you will find a tree

711
00:37:32.960 --> 00:37:36.280
better than any you can dream of.

712
00:37:36.400 --> 00:37:38.800
Better? We gotta go, Belle!

713
00:37:39.080 --> 00:37:40.200
(EXCLAIMS)

714
00:37:40.640 --> 00:37:43.400
-We gotta!
-Chip, we can't.

715
00:37:44.240 --> 00:37:48.080
I... I promised your master
I wouldn't leave the castle grounds.

716
00:37:48.200 --> 00:37:49.320
I gave my word.

717
00:37:49.400 --> 00:37:53.160
FORTE: Chin up, son.
There's a profound lesson here.

718
00:37:53.880 --> 00:37:59.640
Keeping your word is much more
important than bringing joy to another.

719
00:37:59.720 --> 00:38:01.880
You're twisting what I said.

720
00:38:01.960 --> 00:38:04.960
Not at all. I agree with you.

721
00:38:05.040 --> 00:38:09.160
Look after yourself.
Let the master do the same.

722
00:38:09.240 --> 00:38:11.080
Never mind that the tree

723
00:38:11.160 --> 00:38:15.520
was always his favorite part
of Christmas.

724
00:38:15.600 --> 00:38:19.440
Please, Belle? Please?

725
00:38:20.920 --> 00:38:22.800
BELLE: It looks dangerous.

726
00:38:22.880 --> 00:38:27.000
(CHUCKLING) <i>Mademoiselle,</i>
you are in more danger

727
00:38:27.080 --> 00:38:30.480
in this very room, I assure you.

728
00:38:31.880 --> 00:38:32.920
All right.

729
00:38:33.040 --> 00:38:34.840
-Yes!
-We'll take Phillippe.

730
00:38:34.960 --> 00:38:37.000
If we hurry, we can be back by nightfall.

731
00:38:37.080 --> 00:38:40.600
-Hurray!
<i>-Au revoir, Monsieur</i> Forte.

732
00:38:41.120 --> 00:38:43.880
You'll keep my secret, won't you?

733
00:38:44.560 --> 00:38:46.840
Of course, <i>mademoiselle.</i>

734
00:38:46.920 --> 00:38:50.280
The master will remain
completely in the dark.

735
00:38:50.360 --> 00:38:52.160
<i>Au revoir,</i> Fife.

736
00:38:52.960 --> 00:38:54.440
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

737
00:38:54.560 --> 00:38:57.520
Fife! I want you to follow her.

738
00:38:57.840 --> 00:39:01.680
Make sure they don't come back.

739
00:39:01.760 --> 00:39:05.120
Oh, yeah, but, Maestro, she's so nice.

740
00:39:05.200 --> 00:39:07.680
When you're finished fawning, Fife,

741
00:39:07.760 --> 00:39:12.640
perhaps you can recommend
someone else to play your solo.

742
00:39:12.720 --> 00:39:15.120
No! I'm going. I'm going.

743
00:39:15.880 --> 00:39:17.080
(GRUNTS)

744
00:39:17.920 --> 00:39:20.200
(HUMMING <i>DECK THE HALLS)</i>

745
00:39:24.400 --> 00:39:25.640
(HUMMING STOPS)

746
00:39:25.760 --> 00:39:29.800
-Cogsworth!
-Oh, dear. Yes. Coming. Coming.

747
00:39:30.320 --> 00:39:32.680
Cogsworth!

748
00:39:32.760 --> 00:39:37.000
Running, running. Almost there.
You bellowed, sir?

749
00:39:37.080 --> 00:39:40.080
Find Belle. I... Uh...

750
00:39:40.160 --> 00:39:44.400
Well, I... (SIGHS)
She has to hear a song.

751
00:39:44.480 --> 00:39:47.160
Yes, sir. Right away, sir. Uh, yes.

752
00:39:47.640 --> 00:39:50.880
Splendid. Yes, well... Splendid.

753
00:39:50.960 --> 00:39:52.000
Ho-ho-ho-ho-ho-ho.

754
00:39:53.560 --> 00:39:56.000
Belle. Belle?

755
00:39:56.120 --> 00:39:58.280
Where is she? Belle?

756
00:39:59.360 --> 00:40:01.440
LUMIERE: Careful, careful.

757
00:40:01.520 --> 00:40:04.560
Too fast! Get out of the way! Stop!

758
00:40:05.280 --> 00:40:06.280
Huh!

759
00:40:06.360 --> 00:40:07.680
Amateurs.

760
00:40:08.120 --> 00:40:12.200
Belle? Here... Excuse me. Hello?

761
00:40:12.280 --> 00:40:15.640
Has anyone seen Belle?
I can't find her anywhere.

762
00:40:15.720 --> 00:40:17.840
And the master is demanding
to see her now.

763
00:40:17.920 --> 00:40:20.400
-He's got a song he wants her to hear.
-Ho-ho.

764
00:40:20.520 --> 00:40:21.640
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

765
00:40:21.720 --> 00:40:26.680
Last I saw of her, she was going
with Chip to look for a Christmas tree.

766
00:40:26.760 --> 00:40:28.520
(STRAINING)

767
00:40:28.600 --> 00:40:31.360
Right. We must conduct
a search of the grounds.

768
00:40:31.440 --> 00:40:33.200
-Lumiere, you're with me.
-BEAST: Cogsworth!

769
00:40:33.280 --> 00:40:34.320
(GASPS)

770
00:40:34.400 --> 00:40:36.680
I'm waiting!

771
00:40:36.760 --> 00:40:39.880
Oh, dear. Running, running, running.
I'm almost there, sir.

772
00:40:40.840 --> 00:40:43.480
Mrs. Potts, stall the master.
All right, Lumiere, we're...

773
00:40:43.560 --> 00:40:46.240
Lumiere? Wait, I'm leading.

774
00:40:46.320 --> 00:40:48.480
Me first, you second.

775
00:40:49.160 --> 00:40:50.400
(WIND GUSTING)

776
00:40:50.480 --> 00:40:54.360
Belle! Belle! Where is she?

777
00:40:54.440 --> 00:40:57.120
Belle? Belle?

778
00:40:57.200 --> 00:40:58.680
Belle, where are you?

779
00:40:58.760 --> 00:41:00.960
Lumiere, wait.

780
00:41:05.120 --> 00:41:07.040
Hmm? (GASPS)

781
00:41:08.160 --> 00:41:10.400
The Black Forest!

782
00:41:11.120 --> 00:41:13.080
Come along. Hurry now!

783
00:41:14.080 --> 00:41:15.520
(PANTING) Oh, no.

784
00:41:15.600 --> 00:41:17.480
This is catastrophic!

785
00:41:18.400 --> 00:41:20.760
Cogsworth, quit dawdling.

786
00:41:20.840 --> 00:41:23.040
I'm not dawdling. I'm waddling.

787
00:41:23.120 --> 00:41:27.720
Well, don't waddle then.
We're in a hurry, you lazy old clock.

788
00:41:32.360 --> 00:41:33.760
Hmm? Hmm?

789
00:41:35.080 --> 00:41:37.920
Hmm? Hmm?

790
00:41:38.000 --> 00:41:39.880
(CLOCK TICKING)
(SIGHING)

791
00:41:43.760 --> 00:41:46.400
Why am I still waiting?

792
00:41:46.960 --> 00:41:50.200
-Mrs. Potts!
-Coming, sir! Coming!

793
00:41:50.680 --> 00:41:52.640
What a brisk day!

794
00:41:52.720 --> 00:41:56.320
Why, you look positively chilled
to the bone.

795
00:41:56.880 --> 00:41:58.520
Where's Belle?

796
00:41:58.600 --> 00:42:02.520
How about a nice cup of tea, sir?
Just a spot.

797
00:42:02.880 --> 00:42:04.080
Hmm.

798
00:42:05.120 --> 00:42:07.640
Forte, play Belle's song!

799
00:42:10.520 --> 00:42:11.960
BEAST: Hot.

800
00:42:13.480 --> 00:42:15.320
You're not singing!

801
00:42:17.320 --> 00:42:22.440
(SINGING) <i>Deck the halls</i>
<i>with boughs of holly</i>

802
00:42:22.560 --> 00:42:26.280
<i>Fa-la-la-la-la</i>
<i>La-la-la-la</i>

803
00:42:26.400 --> 00:42:27.680
Louder!

804
00:42:28.520 --> 00:42:30.520
<i>'Tis the season</i>

805
00:42:30.600 --> 00:42:33.880
A bit more tea, sir?
Good for the heart, you know.

806
00:42:33.960 --> 00:42:35.080
No, thank you.

807
00:42:35.200 --> 00:42:37.120
-Just a spot?
-No more.

808
00:42:37.240 --> 00:42:40.320
-Well, there's always room for tea, love.
-I said, "No more."

809
00:42:40.400 --> 00:42:42.760
-Oh, dearie me!
-Mrs. Potts,

810
00:42:42.840 --> 00:42:45.800
are you trying to distract me?

811
00:42:45.880 --> 00:42:49.000
Goodness, no, sir. (GASPS)

812
00:42:49.080 --> 00:42:51.960
Heavens. Is that a yellow-bellied,
double-breasted sapsucker?

813
00:42:52.040 --> 00:42:55.160
-Rare this time of year.
-Enough! Where's Cogsworth?

814
00:42:55.240 --> 00:42:57.360
-Where's Belle?
-Belle?

815
00:42:57.440 --> 00:43:01.120
We can't find her, sir.

816
00:43:01.200 --> 00:43:02.640
What?

817
00:43:02.720 --> 00:43:04.040
Leave me!

818
00:43:05.560 --> 00:43:06.640
(GROWLS)

819
00:43:06.720 --> 00:43:08.720
Show me the girl.

820
00:43:10.680 --> 00:43:12.160
(WHINNYING)

821
00:43:14.360 --> 00:43:16.720
-I will bring her back!
-FORTE: No!

822
00:43:16.920 --> 00:43:19.200
Um, she's abandoned you.

823
00:43:19.280 --> 00:43:22.280
-(GROWLS)
-Listen to your old friend, won't you?

824
00:43:22.360 --> 00:43:25.560
Have I ever steered you wrong?
Led you astray?

825
00:43:25.640 --> 00:43:28.480
No. But the girl...

826
00:43:29.040 --> 00:43:33.200
(SINGING) <i>The quickest way</i>
<i>to break your heart</i>

827
00:43:33.280 --> 00:43:36.960
<i>Make you depressed and ill</i>

828
00:43:37.040 --> 00:43:41.160
<i>Is to get tangled up inside</i>

829
00:43:41.240 --> 00:43:45.000
<i>The side effects could kill</i>

830
00:43:45.080 --> 00:43:49.160
<i>All passion is a waste of time</i>

831
00:43:49.240 --> 00:43:51.880
<i>A deadly game</i> pour vous

832
00:43:51.960 --> 00:43:53.000
(LAUGHS)

833
00:43:53.080 --> 00:43:57.360
<i>I am your friend</i>
<i>Your</i> cher ami

834
00:43:57.440 --> 00:44:02.080
<i>I wouldn't lie to you</i>

835
00:44:03.200 --> 00:44:06.520
<i>If you must love someone</i>
<i>may I suggest</i>

836
00:44:06.600 --> 00:44:09.920
<i>You love yourself</i>
<i>Just think it through</i>

837
00:44:10.000 --> 00:44:13.400
<i>You'll never leave</i>
<i>and you will find you'll get more rest</i>

838
00:44:13.480 --> 00:44:16.880
<i>You'll always feel</i>
<i>as good as new</i>

839
00:44:16.960 --> 00:44:20.040
<i>Your freedom is the most</i>
<i>important thing, my friend</i>

840
00:44:20.120 --> 00:44:23.400
<i>You must be strong</i>
<i>You mustn't bend</i>

841
00:44:23.480 --> 00:44:25.480
<i>Don't talk for hours</i>
<i>Don't send flowers</i>

842
00:44:25.600 --> 00:44:27.600
<i>Don't write poems</i>
<i>Don't sing songs and dance</i>

843
00:44:27.680 --> 00:44:30.400
<i>Beneath the stars</i>
<i>that shine above</i>

844
00:44:30.520 --> 00:44:33.480
<i>Don't fall in love</i>

845
00:44:34.000 --> 00:44:37.280
-FORTE: Oh, don't do it.
-(CUPIDS COOING)

846
00:44:37.960 --> 00:44:38.960
Oh!

847
00:44:39.040 --> 00:44:43.280
<i>As soon as your heart</i>
<i>rules your head</i>

848
00:44:43.360 --> 00:44:46.880
<i>Your life is not your own</i>

849
00:44:46.960 --> 00:44:50.800
<i>It's hell when someone's always there</i>

850
00:44:50.880 --> 00:44:54.800
<i>It's bliss to be alone</i>

851
00:44:54.880 --> 00:44:58.840
<i>And love of any kind is bad</i>

852
00:44:58.920 --> 00:45:02.400
<i>A dog, a child, a cat</i>

853
00:45:02.480 --> 00:45:07.000
<i>They take up so much precious time</i>

854
00:45:07.080 --> 00:45:11.560
<i>Now, where's the sense in that</i>

855
00:45:13.560 --> 00:45:16.960
<i>Love takes the wildest heart</i>
<i>and makes it tame</i>

856
00:45:17.040 --> 00:45:20.320
<i>If you're turned on</i>
<i>then just turn off</i>

857
00:45:20.400 --> 00:45:23.880
<i>Emotions are a thing</i>
<i>all great men overcame</i>

858
00:45:23.960 --> 00:45:27.160
<i>Please, don't make</i>
<i>this</i> grande catastrophe

859
00:45:27.240 --> 00:45:30.640
<i>Don't get attached</i>
<i>to anyone or anything</i>

860
00:45:30.720 --> 00:45:34.040
<i>There's nothing worse</i>
<i>than things that cling</i>

861
00:45:34.120 --> 00:45:35.800
<i>You'll go to pot</i>
<i>You'll turn to drink</i>

862
00:45:35.920 --> 00:45:37.520
<i>You'll never rest</i>
<i>You'll end up mad</i>

863
00:45:37.600 --> 00:45:41.280
<i>And looking like</i>
<i>some poor demented dove</i>

864
00:45:41.360 --> 00:45:46.920
<i>Don't fall in love</i>

865
00:45:47.000 --> 00:45:50.160
<i>Don't fall in love!</i>

866
00:45:54.560 --> 00:45:57.360
No, no, no, no, no, no, no.

867
00:45:57.440 --> 00:46:00.600
They cannot mix bells with holly.

868
00:46:00.680 --> 00:46:04.320
Still, I have to admit,
not bad for amateurs.

869
00:46:04.600 --> 00:46:05.880
(BEAST GROWLING)
(GASPS)

870
00:46:06.760 --> 00:46:10.000
(GROWLING)

871
00:46:10.440 --> 00:46:12.120
(GRUNTING)

872
00:46:20.560 --> 00:46:23.360
I knew this was hopeless.

873
00:46:26.760 --> 00:46:28.560
(PHILLIPPE WHINNYING)

874
00:46:34.360 --> 00:46:35.760
(NICKERS)

875
00:46:37.080 --> 00:46:38.400
(WOLVES HOWLING)

876
00:46:38.480 --> 00:46:39.800
(WHIMPERING)

877
00:46:41.560 --> 00:46:42.840
(BARKING)

878
00:46:42.920 --> 00:46:44.120
(HOWLING)

879
00:46:45.480 --> 00:46:46.800
(GROWLING)

880
00:46:54.880 --> 00:46:57.240
There. That's it! That's it!

881
00:47:00.240 --> 00:47:02.800
Oh, Chip, it's perfect.

882
00:47:06.520 --> 00:47:07.680
(GASPING)

883
00:47:07.760 --> 00:47:08.800
(WHINNIES)

884
00:47:09.600 --> 00:47:14.000
-Do you see her?
-Not yet. Now, come along. Hurry!

885
00:47:14.560 --> 00:47:15.960
(COGSWORTH PANTING)

886
00:47:17.520 --> 00:47:20.320
-You go on. I'll never make it.
-(SIGHS)

887
00:47:20.480 --> 00:47:22.160
(COUGHING)

888
00:47:22.680 --> 00:47:23.720
(PANTING)

889
00:47:23.800 --> 00:47:25.320
Save yourself.

890
00:47:26.800 --> 00:47:29.480
Ah, it will be summer
before we reach them.

891
00:47:29.560 --> 00:47:31.320
What the... Whoa!

892
00:47:31.400 --> 00:47:32.480
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

893
00:47:32.560 --> 00:47:33.640
Oh, dear!

894
00:47:34.160 --> 00:47:35.160
(GRUNTS)

895
00:47:35.320 --> 00:47:36.760
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

896
00:47:37.080 --> 00:47:39.640
(LAUGHS) Faster! Faster!

897
00:47:39.720 --> 00:47:42.040
I think we finally found a use for you.

898
00:47:42.120 --> 00:47:44.720
Clock boarding! No, snow clocking!

899
00:47:45.560 --> 00:47:47.040
Whatever!

900
00:47:48.640 --> 00:47:50.520
Whoo! (LAUGHS)

901
00:47:53.160 --> 00:47:55.520
Whoa!

902
00:47:55.840 --> 00:47:56.920
(LAUGHS)

903
00:47:58.000 --> 00:48:02.080
-It's the best tree ever!
-Chip, you're right.

904
00:48:02.160 --> 00:48:06.360
AXE: Merry Christmas!
And a happy Hanukkah!

905
00:48:07.000 --> 00:48:10.160
We better hurry.
It's getting very stormy.

906
00:48:10.240 --> 00:48:12.280
(GROANING)

907
00:48:13.200 --> 00:48:15.280
Again with the chopping.

908
00:48:16.000 --> 00:48:19.640
Oh, I gotta do something.
Forte's counting on me.

909
00:48:19.720 --> 00:48:21.160
(WHINNYING)

910
00:48:22.160 --> 00:48:23.720
(CREAKING)

911
00:48:25.680 --> 00:48:28.160
Timber!

912
00:48:31.520 --> 00:48:32.840
(GRUNTS)

913
00:48:33.680 --> 00:48:34.720
Phew!

914
00:48:34.800 --> 00:48:36.120
(CHIP LAUGHING)

915
00:48:36.200 --> 00:48:38.200
Take it away, Phillippe!

916
00:48:38.280 --> 00:48:39.600
(WHINNIES)

917
00:48:41.080 --> 00:48:42.200
Whoo!

918
00:48:43.520 --> 00:48:44.600
Whoa!

919
00:48:44.680 --> 00:48:46.320
(WHIMPERS)

920
00:48:47.040 --> 00:48:49.160
(WHIMPERING CONTINUES)

921
00:48:50.320 --> 00:48:51.640
Oh, no!

922
00:48:51.880 --> 00:48:53.040
(GRUNTING)

923
00:48:54.720 --> 00:48:56.400
(WHIMPERING)

924
00:48:58.360 --> 00:49:00.680
Aah! Aah! Aaah!

925
00:49:04.880 --> 00:49:06.160
Fife?

926
00:49:06.240 --> 00:49:08.200
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)
Uh, hi, Belle.

927
00:49:08.880 --> 00:49:10.400
Nice tree.

928
00:49:10.960 --> 00:49:12.840
What are you doing way out here?

929
00:49:12.920 --> 00:49:15.840
Uh, nothin'. I just was walkin'.

930
00:49:15.920 --> 00:49:19.120
I mean, I love the bitter cold. I mean...
Hee, hee!

931
00:49:19.200 --> 00:49:20.560
(TOOTS)
(SHRIEKS)

932
00:49:21.520 --> 00:49:22.680
(BLOWS)
(SHRIEKS)

933
00:49:22.760 --> 00:49:24.080
(WHINNYING)

934
00:49:25.240 --> 00:49:26.800
Phillippe!

935
00:49:31.320 --> 00:49:32.760
Oh, no!

936
00:49:33.480 --> 00:49:34.640
(SNORTS)

937
00:49:36.760 --> 00:49:39.680
CHIP: The tree, Belle!
We're gonna lose the tree!

938
00:49:39.760 --> 00:49:41.320
Whoa!

939
00:49:42.160 --> 00:49:44.160
Chip! Oh!

940
00:49:45.240 --> 00:49:46.680
Where is he?

941
00:49:46.760 --> 00:49:49.120
Whoa! Whoa!

942
00:50:05.120 --> 00:50:06.680
(MUFFLED SHOUTING)

943
00:50:07.280 --> 00:50:08.480
BELLE: Oh!

944
00:50:09.800 --> 00:50:10.880
(WHIMPERING)

945
00:50:14.880 --> 00:50:18.720
-Hold on, <i>ch√©rie.</i> I will save you!
-Oh, dear!

946
00:50:19.320 --> 00:50:22.800
Oh, no. Oh, gosh. Oh, no.
Oh, gosh. Oh, no. Oh, gosh.

947
00:50:23.240 --> 00:50:24.560
Oh, no!

948
00:50:25.920 --> 00:50:27.080
(BLOWING)

949
00:50:27.280 --> 00:50:28.320
(EXCLAIMS)

950
00:50:31.200 --> 00:50:32.280
(GASPS)

951
00:50:34.560 --> 00:50:35.560
(COUGHING)

952
00:50:35.680 --> 00:50:40.120
-Oh, Chip, thank goodness you're safe.
-I wasn't scared.

953
00:50:43.160 --> 00:50:44.160
(GASPS)

954
00:50:44.240 --> 00:50:45.880
Oh, no! No!

955
00:50:47.120 --> 00:50:48.200
(GRUNTING)

956
00:50:50.000 --> 00:50:51.720
(GROWLING)

957
00:51:04.080 --> 00:51:05.520
(GROWLING)

958
00:51:11.320 --> 00:51:12.680
Belle!

959
00:51:15.200 --> 00:51:16.360
(GASPS)

960
00:51:24.200 --> 00:51:27.120
Oh, no, what have I done?

961
00:51:28.040 --> 00:51:29.800
It's all my fault.

962
00:51:29.880 --> 00:51:35.320
We all share some blame, <i>mon ami,</i>
for daring to hope for a Christmas.

963
00:51:57.400 --> 00:51:59.880
You said you'd never leave.

964
00:52:04.160 --> 00:52:06.480
I wasn't trying to leave.

965
00:52:08.320 --> 00:52:11.040
I just wanted to make you happy.

966
00:52:13.520 --> 00:52:16.640
You broke your word.

967
00:52:16.720 --> 00:52:22.200
And for that, you will rot
in this dungeon forever.

968
00:52:24.080 --> 00:52:28.600
I should have known
you'd never be anything but a beast.

969
00:52:28.960 --> 00:52:30.440
(BELL TOLLING)

970
00:52:33.200 --> 00:52:34.200
(SIGHS)

971
00:52:34.280 --> 00:52:36.120
Midnight.

972
00:52:36.200 --> 00:52:38.640
Merry Christmas, Cogsworth.

973
00:52:39.080 --> 00:52:41.040
If only it were.

974
00:52:43.600 --> 00:52:49.200
FORTE: Oh, my dear old friend,
I told you not to feel for her.

975
00:52:49.840 --> 00:52:54.480
Things were so much simpler
before she came along,

976
00:52:54.560 --> 00:52:58.560
before we dared to hope.

977
00:52:59.200 --> 00:53:03.440
Oh, I thought she was the one.

978
00:53:05.600 --> 00:53:06.600
Belle?

979
00:53:06.680 --> 00:53:07.680
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

980
00:53:07.760 --> 00:53:09.680
MRS. POTTS: There she is.

981
00:53:09.760 --> 00:53:14.200
-Merry Christmas.
-Doesn't look so special to me.

982
00:53:14.800 --> 00:53:19.080
Oh, Chip, I'm sorry.

983
00:53:19.760 --> 00:53:21.440
Nothing's changed.

984
00:53:21.520 --> 00:53:24.200
I told you nothing would change.

985
00:53:24.280 --> 00:53:26.240
I told you the master
would not allow this.

986
00:53:26.320 --> 00:53:29.840
I told you
Christmas was a hopeless folly!

987
00:53:30.840 --> 00:53:32.160
But

988
00:53:33.520 --> 00:53:35.040
I was wrong.

989
00:53:38.400 --> 00:53:42.400
(SINGING) <i>When I felt lost</i>

990
00:53:42.480 --> 00:53:45.520
<i>And lonely</i>

991
00:53:45.600 --> 00:53:50.920
<i>Not a dream in my head</i>

992
00:53:52.240 --> 00:53:57.120
<i>Your words lifted my spirits</i>

993
00:53:57.200 --> 00:53:59.320
<i>High</i>

994
00:53:59.400 --> 00:54:02.280
<i>Remember what</i>

995
00:54:02.360 --> 00:54:04.800
<i>You said</i>

996
00:54:06.440 --> 00:54:12.680
<i>As long as there's Christmas</i>

997
00:54:12.760 --> 00:54:17.720
<i>I truly believe</i>

998
00:54:18.720 --> 00:54:24.440
<i>That hope is the greatest</i>

999
00:54:24.520 --> 00:54:30.600
<i>Of the gifts we'll receive</i>

1000
00:54:31.440 --> 00:54:34.320
<i>-As long as</i>
<i>-As long as</i>

1001
00:54:34.400 --> 00:54:38.640
<i>Our guiding star</i>

1002
00:54:38.720 --> 00:54:43.360
<i>Shines above</i>

1003
00:54:43.440 --> 00:54:47.080
<i>There'll always be</i>

1004
00:54:47.160 --> 00:54:53.440
<i>Christmas</i>

1005
00:54:53.560 --> 00:54:56.840
<i>So there always</i>

1006
00:54:56.920 --> 00:55:00.120
<i>Will be a time</i>

1007
00:55:00.200 --> 00:55:06.000
<i>When the world</i>
<i>is filled with peace</i>

1008
00:55:06.720 --> 00:55:13.400
<i>And love</i>

1009
00:55:19.200 --> 00:55:24.360
Ah, it tears me up
to see you this way, master.

1010
00:55:24.440 --> 00:55:26.600
Why do you torment yourself?

1011
00:55:26.720 --> 00:55:29.720
There's the symbol of your curse.

1012
00:55:29.800 --> 00:55:33.520
Destroy it, and end
these adolescent notions

1013
00:55:33.600 --> 00:55:36.920
of love and redemption.

1014
00:55:37.000 --> 00:55:40.800
End your pain forever.

1015
00:55:43.120 --> 00:55:45.520
Yes! Do it!

1016
00:55:45.600 --> 00:55:46.600
(GROWLS)

1017
00:55:46.680 --> 00:55:49.080
Smash it!

1018
00:55:49.320 --> 00:55:50.760
(GROWLING)

1019
00:55:56.960 --> 00:55:58.560
Belle?

1020
00:55:59.920 --> 00:56:01.600
(THUDDING)

1021
00:56:01.680 --> 00:56:04.080
What are you doing? What is it?

1022
00:56:09.120 --> 00:56:12.360
Oh, a storybook.

1023
00:56:12.440 --> 00:56:16.480
Does this one have pretty pictures
you can color? (LAUGHS)

1024
00:56:16.560 --> 00:56:19.080
Utterly dreadful, master.

1025
00:56:19.160 --> 00:56:24.040
No! This one's different. It's from Belle.

1026
00:56:24.120 --> 00:56:27.640
Well, that would account
for the creative wrapping.

1027
00:56:27.720 --> 00:56:29.920
Quiet! (GROWLS)

1028
00:56:31.600 --> 00:56:33.120
I want to read.

1029
00:56:33.240 --> 00:56:34.360
(SIGHS)

1030
00:56:35.160 --> 00:56:37.280
(FIRE CRACKLING)

1031
00:56:38.560 --> 00:56:42.640
BELLE'S VOICE: <i>"Once upon a time,</i>
<i>there was an enchanted castle.</i>

1032
00:56:42.720 --> 00:56:47.200
<i>"Its master seemed as cold as winter.</i>
<i>Deep inside his heart...</i>

1033
00:56:47.280 --> 00:56:50.440
<i>"His cries of anger echoed through</i>
<i>the stone wall of the castle.</i>

1034
00:56:50.520 --> 00:56:54.960
<i>"Though surrounded by servants,</i>
<i>he was all alone.</i>

1035
00:56:55.040 --> 00:56:58.040
<i>"And in that simple act of kindness,</i>

1036
00:56:58.120 --> 00:57:00.680
<i>"he knew someone cared.</i>

1037
00:57:00.760 --> 00:57:04.640
<i>"Christmas that year was spent</i>
<i>exchanging humble gifts.</i>

1038
00:57:04.720 --> 00:57:07.960
<i>"But the greatest gift</i>
<i>that anyone received</i>

1039
00:57:08.040 --> 00:57:10.880
<i>"was the gift of hope."</i>

1040
00:57:12.960 --> 00:57:14.320
(FIRE CRACKLING)

1041
00:57:14.400 --> 00:57:15.400
Hmm.

1042
00:57:15.720 --> 00:57:17.040
Hope.

1043
00:57:24.800 --> 00:57:27.000
-No, master! Come back!
-(DOOR OPENS)

1044
00:57:27.080 --> 00:57:30.000
She'll only prolong your torment!

1045
00:57:30.440 --> 00:57:35.400
You know what, Belle? I don't need
a tree to celebrate Christmas.

1046
00:57:35.480 --> 00:57:39.280
-And I can do without mistletoe.
-(BELL CHIMES)

1047
00:57:39.360 --> 00:57:42.240
-Well, I don't need tinsel.
-Oh, I don't need holly.

1048
00:57:42.320 --> 00:57:44.680
-And I don't need a wreath.
-I don't need ornaments!

1049
00:57:44.760 --> 00:57:47.680
-And I don't need turkey!
-I don't need stuffing!

1050
00:57:47.760 --> 00:57:50.880
I don't need pudding!

1051
00:57:50.960 --> 00:57:53.520
(SINGING) <i>To each his own, my friend</i>
<i>You know how to get me stressed</i>

1052
00:57:53.600 --> 00:57:54.600
(RASPBERRY)

1053
00:57:54.680 --> 00:57:56.840
<i>But when it comes to</i>
<i>making Christmas special...</i>

1054
00:57:56.920 --> 00:57:58.520
<i>I'm a cut above the rest</i>

1055
00:57:58.600 --> 00:58:01.840
<i>If you could see things clearly</i>
<i>you would say that I've been blessed</i>

1056
00:58:01.920 --> 00:58:04.680
<i>You can't hold a candle</i>
<i>to my timing</i>

1057
00:58:04.760 --> 00:58:07.240
<i>I'm a cut above the rest</i>

1058
00:58:07.320 --> 00:58:10.960
<i>You belong side by side</i>
<i>You should never be apart</i>

1059
00:58:11.040 --> 00:58:15.280
<i>'Cause when you're both together</i>
<i>you're really twice as smart</i>

1060
00:58:15.360 --> 00:58:18.360
"Twice as smart."
She does have a point.

1061
00:58:18.440 --> 00:58:21.720
Yes, well, two heads
are better than one.

1062
00:58:21.800 --> 00:58:25.000
<i>They say that as a team</i>
<i>we have got to be the best</i>

1063
00:58:25.080 --> 00:58:27.600
<i>Now we found something</i>
<i>we both agree on</i>

1064
00:58:27.680 --> 00:58:29.200
<i>We're a cut above the rest</i>

1065
00:58:29.280 --> 00:58:32.800
<i>There's no doubt that as a team</i>
<i>we two are the very best</i>

1066
00:58:32.880 --> 00:58:35.280
<i>Everyone who knows us must agree</i>

1067
00:58:35.360 --> 00:58:36.960
<i>We're a cut above the rest</i>

1068
00:58:37.040 --> 00:58:40.400
<i>There's no doubt that as a team</i>
<i>you two are the very best</i>

1069
00:58:40.480 --> 00:58:43.080
<i>Everyone who knows you must agree</i>

1070
00:58:43.160 --> 00:58:45.440
<i>-We're a cut</i>
<i>-A cut above</i>

1071
00:58:45.520 --> 00:58:47.200
<i>Above the rest</i>

1072
00:58:49.840 --> 00:58:51.960
Uh-oh! It's the master!

1073
00:58:52.840 --> 00:58:55.440
Uh, Belle...

1074
00:59:06.040 --> 00:59:08.200
Can you forgive me?

1075
00:59:13.520 --> 00:59:14.760
(CHUCKLES)

1076
00:59:15.280 --> 00:59:18.600
Of course. Merry Christmas.

1077
00:59:19.120 --> 00:59:20.360
-(CHEERING)
-CHIP: All right!

1078
00:59:20.720 --> 00:59:24.160
Let's give Belle the Christmas
she's always wanted.

1079
00:59:25.040 --> 00:59:27.400
FORTE: So, Beast gets girl,

1080
00:59:27.480 --> 00:59:30.600
and it's a happy ending for everyone.

1081
00:59:31.240 --> 00:59:33.680
Enchantment lifted,

1082
00:59:34.360 --> 00:59:37.800
and Forte fades into the background.

1083
00:59:38.280 --> 00:59:43.200
No longer important. No longer needed.

1084
00:59:43.880 --> 00:59:45.960
I think not!

1085
00:59:46.200 --> 00:59:48.280
(MUSIC BLARING)

1086
00:59:56.360 --> 00:59:59.120
What is it, Mama? What's happening?

1087
00:59:59.240 --> 01:00:00.880
(FORTE LAUGHING)

1088
01:00:04.680 --> 01:00:06.200
Watch out!

1089
01:00:08.120 --> 01:00:09.480
Forte!

1090
01:00:09.560 --> 01:00:11.520
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

1091
01:00:11.600 --> 01:00:12.640
(GASPS)

1092
01:00:12.720 --> 01:00:14.800
-Whoa!
-Hurry, now. Hurry.

1093
01:00:16.560 --> 01:00:19.760
Can you believe I never took a lesson?

1094
01:00:19.840 --> 01:00:21.120
(GRUNTING)

1095
01:00:22.080 --> 01:00:23.160
(GROWLING)

1096
01:00:23.240 --> 01:00:24.560
Belle!

1097
01:00:25.440 --> 01:00:26.680
-BELLE: Oh, no!
-Belle!

1098
01:00:26.760 --> 01:00:27.920
Help!

1099
01:00:31.080 --> 01:00:32.440
(WHIMPERING)

1100
01:00:35.080 --> 01:00:36.800
(WHIMPERING CONTINUES)

1101
01:00:37.480 --> 01:00:38.600
(BLOWS)

1102
01:00:39.120 --> 01:00:40.160
Oh, no.

1103
01:00:41.000 --> 01:00:43.520
(FORTE CONTINUES PLAYING)

1104
01:00:43.600 --> 01:00:46.120
Maestro! Stop!

1105
01:00:47.120 --> 01:00:51.040
-What do you think you're doing?
-Don't you see, Fife?

1106
01:00:51.120 --> 01:00:54.400
They can't fall in love if they're dead.

1107
01:00:54.480 --> 01:00:58.560
I'll tell you what I see.
A big, old windbag!

1108
01:00:58.640 --> 01:00:59.800
(LAUGHS NERVOUSLY)

1109
01:00:59.880 --> 01:01:02.480
You could've joined me, Fife,

1110
01:01:02.560 --> 01:01:06.440
but I see my triumph is a solo act.

1111
01:01:08.280 --> 01:01:10.760
My solo... It's blank!

1112
01:01:10.840 --> 01:01:11.920
(FORTE LAUGHS)

1113
01:01:12.000 --> 01:01:13.720
So naive.

1114
01:01:13.800 --> 01:01:16.400
-No! No, no!
-You're second fiddle, Fife,

1115
01:01:16.480 --> 01:01:19.400
and that's all you'll ever be.

1116
01:01:19.480 --> 01:01:21.480
Forte!

1117
01:01:25.120 --> 01:01:30.240
We can remain as we are
forever and ever!

1118
01:01:30.560 --> 01:01:32.000
(LAUGHING SINISTERLY)

1119
01:01:35.840 --> 01:01:37.840
BEAST: Forte!

1120
01:01:43.840 --> 01:01:45.720
Enough! (GROWLS)

1121
01:01:45.800 --> 01:01:47.840
Heavens! Master.

1122
01:01:49.320 --> 01:01:51.640
You're not singing.

1123
01:01:58.000 --> 01:01:59.120
(GRUNTS)

1124
01:01:59.960 --> 01:02:01.360
(PANTING)

1125
01:02:02.080 --> 01:02:03.480
Careful.

1126
01:02:08.520 --> 01:02:09.760
(GROWLING)

1127
01:02:11.360 --> 01:02:13.400
LUMIERE: Oh, no, the bell jar!

1128
01:02:13.480 --> 01:02:17.120
-Whoa! Got it. Got it.
-Oh, careful.

1129
01:02:17.200 --> 01:02:20.200
Is this happy enough for you, master?

1130
01:02:20.280 --> 01:02:24.720
I know I'm downright giddy!

1131
01:02:24.800 --> 01:02:25.960
(GROWLING)

1132
01:02:26.520 --> 01:02:27.520
Oh!

1133
01:02:27.600 --> 01:02:29.920
Master, the keyboard.

1134
01:02:30.360 --> 01:02:31.520
(GROWLING)

1135
01:02:31.600 --> 01:02:33.320
(LAUGHING SINISTERLY)

1136
01:02:35.560 --> 01:02:37.800
(LAUGHING CONTINUES)

1137
01:02:46.600 --> 01:02:47.960
(CLICKING)

1138
01:02:48.480 --> 01:02:49.720
(GASPING)

1139
01:02:54.520 --> 01:02:56.640
-LUMIERE: You got it?
-Got it. Got it.

1140
01:02:57.160 --> 01:02:58.360
Whoa!

1141
01:03:01.040 --> 01:03:02.560
(GROWLING)

1142
01:03:05.680 --> 01:03:07.080
(GASPING) Help!

1143
01:03:09.600 --> 01:03:10.880
(SCREAMING)

1144
01:03:11.400 --> 01:03:15.200
No!

1145
01:03:24.040 --> 01:03:25.440
Forte.

1146
01:03:32.520 --> 01:03:35.480
Oh, yes, it is lovely.

1147
01:03:35.560 --> 01:03:38.000
And you said it was impossible.

1148
01:03:38.120 --> 01:03:39.640
Uh-uh-uh-uh.

1149
01:03:39.960 --> 01:03:44.160
I said it was impossible without me.

1150
01:03:44.560 --> 01:03:47.680
-Everyone, shh-shh! Here they come.
-Wow!

1151
01:03:47.960 --> 01:03:49.040
(MURMURING)

1152
01:03:49.120 --> 01:03:50.120
(GRUNTING)

1153
01:03:50.200 --> 01:03:52.240
COGSWORTH: The setting is perfect.

1154
01:03:52.800 --> 01:03:55.120
Oh, aren't they beautiful?

1155
01:03:59.000 --> 01:04:00.040
(GASPS)

1156
01:04:00.120 --> 01:04:02.320
-It's wonderful!
-(ALL LAUGHING)

1157
01:04:02.440 --> 01:04:04.160
Hurray!

1158
01:04:04.240 --> 01:04:05.480
(ALL CHEERING)

1159
01:04:06.960 --> 01:04:09.720
And what a wonderful Christmas it was.

1160
01:04:09.800 --> 01:04:15.240
I suppose if anyone saved Christmas,
it was Belle.

1161
01:04:15.320 --> 01:04:17.640
Merry Christmas, one and all!

1162
01:04:17.720 --> 01:04:20.720
-Merry Christmas.
-And merry Christmas to you, sir.

1163
01:04:20.800 --> 01:04:23.480
MRS. POTTS: Merry Christmas.
LUMIERE: Merry Christmas, everyone.

1164
01:04:23.560 --> 01:04:27.280
I believe we have
a little something for you, Chip.

1165
01:04:27.360 --> 01:04:30.400
A present? Oh, boy! Thank you.

1166
01:04:30.480 --> 01:04:32.080
WOMAN: Open it!

1167
01:04:32.160 --> 01:04:33.480
(CHATTERING)

1168
01:04:33.600 --> 01:04:37.400
Look, Mama! A storybook!
Would you read it to me?

1169
01:04:37.520 --> 01:04:40.120
-I'd love to, son.
-Oh, boy!

1170
01:04:40.200 --> 01:04:41.880
(INDISTINCT LAUGHING)

1171
01:04:44.520 --> 01:04:46.080
Maestro?

1172
01:04:48.240 --> 01:04:51.720
-Yes, master?
-Would you do us the honor, old friend?

1173
01:04:52.400 --> 01:04:54.160
I'd be delighted.

1174
01:04:54.240 --> 01:04:55.320
(LAUGHS)

1175
01:05:41.080 --> 01:05:43.120
(SOULFUL CHRISTMAS MUSIC
PLAYING)

